               kpred:measured     "MEASURED 2026-07-12 (compress.test.ts): the compression FORMAT saves ~18% vs grouped Turtle (what a real .ttl looks like) and ~29% vs flat one-triple-per-line Turtle. The docs previously claimed ~60-70%, which was WRONG for the format — that figure conflated the encoding with SUBGRAPH SELECTION, which is where the large saving actually comes from (returning a relevant slice instead of the whole ~116k-token graph). Selection is the headline; the format is a modest, real win on top of it. The test asserts a >=15% floor, so if the encoding ever regresses below what we claim, CI says so." ;
