               kpred:description  "FUTURE / enterprise-only: a group of people vote on a decision (e.g. approving a proposed fact, promotion, or roadmap change). Requires RBAC and bring-your-own authentication provider (SSO/LDAP/OIDC). Votes and outcomes modeled as graph entities. Deprioritized in favor of mobile UI/UX work — noted here so the intent is not lost." ;
               kpred:relates-to   kb:enterprise-3ps .

kb:mobile-uiux rdf:type ktype:Feature ;
               rdfs:label    "Mobile UI/UX Architecture" ;
               kpred:feature-id   "F36" ;
               kpred:has-status   "planned" ;
               kpred:priority     "high" ;
               kpred:description  "Make Reckons.AI genuinely usable on mobile by fixing how the app uses its UI libraries. DIAGNOSIS (measured 2026-07-07): no shared breakpoint system — 23 hand-rolled @media blocks across ~10 arbitrary px breakpoints (600/640/500/900/380/420...) vs a single Tailwind responsive prefix; Tailwind v4 is installed but its responsive system is effectively unused; no useMediaQuery/viewport store and no @theme screens tokens. SnapPanel is a px-width position:fixed floating window dragged via MOUSE events (clientX/clientY, no touch) that snaps to corners computed from window.innerWidth — unusable on a phone. 18 fixed/absolute floating panels stacked by z-index (300-500) overlap instead of reflowing. bits-ui Dialog/Popover/Select/Tooltip are used as desktop patterns (center modals, hover tooltips) with no mobile sheet/drawer equivalent. ARCHITECTURE (phased): (1) FOUNDATION — one breakpoint source of truth: Tailwind @theme screens tokens + CSS custom-media + a Svelte 5 viewport rune store (isMobile / isTouch / breakpoint via matchMedia + pointer:coarse). (2) ADAPTIVE PRIMITIVES — a Sheet/Drawer primitive (bits-ui Dialog styled as a bottom sheet) and an AdaptivePanel wrapper that renders SnapPanel on desktop but a bottom sheet / full-screen drawer on mobile; Select -> sheet/native picker on mobile; Tooltip -> tap-to-reveal or dropped on coarse pointers. (3) INPUT — replace SnapPanel mouse-drag with Pointer Events (touch + mouse) and disable free-drag on mobile in favor of the sheet. (4) LAYOUT — single-column reflow below 640px, primary actions in the thumb zone, touch gestures on the 2D/3D graph, >= 44px targets. Verified by F34 deep tests against the mobile-tagged guidelines in kb:web-uiux-rubric (touch-targets, responsive-layout, progressive-disclosure). Prioritized over F35 steering-committee." ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:visual-testing ;
               kpred:relates-to   kb:deep-testing ;
               kpred:decided      "PWA orientation = 'any' (was 'portrait', vite.config.ts). Reckons.AI is a force-directed GRAPH app — locking portrait is exactly wrong for the thing users most want to do on a tablet. Consequence Matt flagged: MORE visual tests to run per device type — the device matrix (F34 deep testing) must now cover BOTH orientations per device, not just portrait. (Matt, 2026-07-15.)" .

